IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Attachments -NCMEC Cybertip # }br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--> 154680560 -Comcast Subpoena (draft) Narrative On 2/24/23, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTip # }br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--> 154680560. The Cyber Tip, generated by Comcast, indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet. The CyberTip was assigned to TFC Cooke #6272 for investigation. The CyberTip provided the following information pertaining to the suspect: Address: US Email Address: chamar123457489@gmail.com Screen/User Name: ddot1333 IP Address: 76.100.218.8 (Login) 11-24-2022 03:46:56 UTC The CyberTip contained 1 reported child pornography file. TFC Cooke reviewed the reported child pornography files and determined that it constitutes child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. The file is described below: Filename:71969098888601792461546805600.mp4 Description: 5 second video file showing an apparent black male exposing his penis and touching it with his thumb. The males penis is underdeveloped with minimal pubic hair. Reasonably believed to be 10 - 12 years of age. The CyberTip indicated that the following IP address 76.100.218.8 (11-24-2022 04:51:41 UTC) was utilized to upload the reported contraband file. TFC Cooke conducted a query of the upload IP address through an open-source database and determined that it is registered through Comcast and geo-locates generally to the District Heights area of Prince Georges County, Maryland. TFC Cooke transmitted an investigative subpoena request to the Howard County Office of the States Attorney for Comcast subscriber information. Case Status OPEN / PENDING ADDITIONAL INVESTIGATION

On 3/6/23, Comcast provided subscriber information: Subscriber Name: ALESE CHAMBLISS Service Address: 6505 FOSTER ST DISTRICT HEIGHTS, MD 207472240 Billing Address: 6505 FOSTER ST DISTRICT HEIGHTS, MD 20747 Telephone #: (240) 223-7144 TFC Cooke contacted Alese Chambliss who advised that her 8 year-old great-grandson, Chamar, had uploaded the video of himself to Tiktok. Chambliss advised that she would speak with her grand-daughter, Chamars mother, about the incident. Internet safety talk provided. Case closed by exception. All events occurred in Prince Georges County, MD.
